-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/eramet-s-gabon-unit-says-first-half-manganese-alloy-production-rises-2-7-.html
Comilog Gabon, a mining venture
controlled by  Eramet (ERA)  SA and the Gabonese government, increased
first-half manganese alloy production 2.7 percent to 415,000
metric tons from a year earlier, the company said in a
statement.  Manganese sales rose 5.4 percent to 411,000 tons, it said
in a statement broadcast on Radio Television Gabonaise
yesterday. Manganese ore and sinter production climbed 7 percent
to 1.68 million tons, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Antoine Lawson in Libreville at 
 ankolo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
